or of Science in Civil Engineering  BSCE  at UIC is accredited by the Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology  ABET  a necessary requirement for obtaining the Professional Engineering  PE  license  The program educational objectives and student outcomes for the BSCE degree program at UIC were approved by the Departmental faculty  Civil Engineering Professional Advisory Council  CEPAC  and student representatives of the Department  and they are detailed under ABET Accreditation page CEPAC ABET Accreditation Apply now GETTING STARTED Undergraduate Admissions Undergraduate Catalog   nFrequently Asked Questions n Frequently Asked Questions DEGREE REQUIREMENTS  nDegree Requirements n Degree Requirements Curriculum Flowchart  nSample Course Schedule n Sample Course Schedule  nSchedule of Class n Schedule of Class CONCENTRATION AREAS Environmental and Water Resources Engineering  as well as design of hydraulic structures and systems to handle hydrologic flow Core Elective Courses   nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME     Geotechnical Engineering  site characterization  analysis and design of shallow and deep foundations and earth retaining structures  environmental laws and regulations  sources of environmental contamination and waste treatment options Core Elective Courses   nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME     Structural Engineering Structural Engineering includes design of metal  masonry  bridge design  pre stressed concrete design  advanced methods of structural analysis and preparation for passing the PE and SE exams Core Elective Courses   nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME      nCME     n CME     Transportation Engineering Transportation Engineering covers geometric design of highways  traffic engineering and control  study of driver  vehicle and roadway system characteristics  intersection design and operation  highway capacity analysis and traffic signal